# Changelog

All notable changes to this project will be documented in this file when possible.

The format is based on Keep a Changelog:
https://keepachangelog.com/en/1.1.0/

## [Unreleased]

### Added
- Added an experimental NumPy-only ``FieldVoxelGrid`` prototype for scalar,
  vector, and matrix-valued voxel fields.
- Added ``VectorVoxelGrid`` as a convenience field grid for three-component
  vector fields, including atom-normal sphere masks and Matplotlib quiver
  plotting helpers.

### Changed
- None.

### Fixed
- None.

## [0.2.8] - 2026-06-30

### Added
- Added ``dtype`` support for voxel grids, including integer, floating, and
  complex NumPy dtypes where backend support is available.
- Added a dtype benchmark script for comparing grid storage types.
- Documented dtype behavior and performance considerations.

### Changed
- Complex grids now support arithmetic sphere operations but reject ordered
  operations such as ``min_sphere``, ``clamp_grid``, range sampling, and
  threshold plotting.

## [0.2.7] - 2026-06-29

### Added
- First public release in a documentation ready state
- Taichi, CuPy, and Numba accelerators implemented
